This video of CNN producer Tawanda Scott Sambou's daughter talking to a friend about COVID-19 is heartbreaking.  We need to address this problem head on.  https://t.co/IThjB2DJIL,2020-04-26 13:44:54,Twitter Web App,99,334,covid; 
When your job is to save lives you don’t say stupid stuff like this...unless you think your job is just to get attention. #V0TE   Trump asked if disinfectants could be injected to kill the coronavirus inside the body. Doctors answered: ‘People will die”  https://t.co/T4XSLws2TY,2020-04-24 12:06:27,Twitter for iPhone,975,4913,corona; 
Great development today in MN as Gov. @Tim_Walz @UMNews &amp; @MayoClinic announced a joint effort to increase coronavirus testing capacity. I am proud of the innovation &amp; work happening here to scale-up testing for COVID-19. This is an important step in helping our economy reopen. https://t.co/5fso6s921e,2020-04-23 01:12:00,Twitter for iPhone,113,746,covid; corona; 
Many veterans are vulnerable to COVID-19 especially those exposed to burn pits. And a major part of getting them help goes back to testing. I want to ensure we get tests out to people caring for our veterans so we can prevent our vulnerable populations from getting sick. https://t.co/HJfsi60unw,2020-04-22 20:47:01,Twitter Media Studio,120,440,covid; 
Workers in the food supply industry are facing increased threats of COVID-19 as more cases emerge in meatpacking &amp; processing plants. They need testing protective equipment &amp; strong safety standards. I’m calling on the Administration to take action to make sure workers are safe.,2020-04-22 20:07:32,Twitter Web App,173,880,covid; 
Rural America shouldn't fight this crisis alone. Making sure they have resources information &amp; funding is vital. That’s why @repdelgado @RepTorresSmall &amp; I are urging the @USDA to establish a Rural COVID-19 Task Force to help tackle this crisis. https://t.co/SRsqZ7k8M8,2020-04-21 22:37:29,Twitter Web App,125,613,covid; 
Everyone is at risk of getting this virus. Minnesota’s first case was healthy Ironman athlete Ben O'Donnell who nearly died from the virus. Ben thank you for sharing your story &amp; donating your blood to help others who are facing COVID-19. https://t.co/4ZXRjc1272,2020-04-21 01:07:58,Twitter Web App,997,3254,covid; 
Albany GA a small town that's predominantly African American saw some of the highest rates of COVID-19 cases in the country. Rural communities of color must receive the resources they need to fight this crisis &amp; I'm working to make sure they get them.  https://t.co/EvqHUHBQ0G,2020-04-20 23:06:52,Twitter for iPhone,137,539,covid; 
